Data loading

weather_df = 
  rnoaa::meteo_pull_monitors(
    c("USW00094728", "USW00022534", "USS0023B17S"),
    var = c("PRCP", "TMIN", "TMAX"), 
    date_min = "2021-01-01",
    date_max = "2022-12-31") |>
  mutate(
    name = recode(
      id, 
      USW00094728 = "CentralPark_NY", 
      USW00022534 = "Molokai_HI",
      USS0023B17S = "Waterhole_WA"),
    tmin = tmin / 10,
    tmax = tmax / 10) |>
  select(name, id, everything())

Basic plot

#Scatterplot
ggplot(weather_df, aes(x = tmin, y = tmax)) +
  geom_point()
## Warning: Removed 17 rows containing missing values (`geom_point()`).

#use geom_hex() when data size much larger
#Use pipe to plot
weather_df |>
  filter(name == "CentralPark_NY") |> 
  ggplot(aes(x = tmin, y = tmax)) + 
  geom_point()

# Advanced plots

ggplot(weather_df, aes(x=tmin, y=tmax))+
  geom_point(aes(color=name),alpha=0.3)+ #only points colored by name not the smooth line
  #alpha: transparent dots
  geom_smooth(se = FALSE) #get rid of error bars at the beginning
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'gam' and formula = 'y ~ s(x, bs = "cs")'
## Warning: Removed 17 rows containing non-finite values (`stat_smooth()`).
## Warning: Removed 17 rows containing missing values (`geom_point()`).

#facets
ggplot(weather_df, aes(x=tmin,y=tmax,color=name))+
  geom_point(alpha=0.3)+
  geom_smooth()+
  facet_grid(.~name)
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula = 'y ~ x'
## Warning: Removed 17 rows containing non-finite values (`stat_smooth()`).
## Removed 17 rows containing missing values (`geom_point()`).

ggplot(weather_df, aes(x = date, y = tmax, color = name)) + 
  geom_point(aes(size=prcp),alpha=0.3)+
  geom_smooth()+
  facet_grid(.~name)
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula = 'y ~ x'
## Warning: Removed 17 rows containing non-finite values (`stat_smooth()`).
## Warning: Removed 19 rows containing missing values (`geom_point()`).

weather_df |> 
  filter(name=="CentralPark_NY") |> 
  mutate(
    tmax_fahr = tmax * (9 / 5) + 32,
    tmin_fahr = tmin * (9 / 5) + 32) |> 
  ggplot(aes(x=tmin_fahr, y=tmax_fahr))+
  geom_point(alpha=0.3)+
  geom_smooth()
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula = 'y ~ x'

# Univariate plotting

ggplot(weather_df,aes(x=tmax, fill=name))+
  geom_histogram(position = "dodge") #dodge is not stacking columns
## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.
## Warning: Removed 17 rows containing non-finite values (`stat_bin()`).

#density plot
ggplot(weather_df,aes(x=tmax, fill=name))+
  geom_density(alpha=0.3)
## Warning: Removed 17 rows containing non-finite values (`stat_density()`).

#box plot
ggplot(weather_df,aes(y=tmax, x=name))+
  geom_boxplot()
## Warning: Removed 17 rows containing non-finite values (`stat_boxplot()`).

#violin plot: reverse of density plot
ggplot(weather_df, aes(x = name, y = tmax)) + 
  geom_violin(aes(fill = name), alpha = .5) + 
  stat_summary(fun = "median", color = "blue")
## Warning: Removed 17 rows containing non-finite values (`stat_ydensity()`).
## Warning: Removed 17 rows containing non-finite values (`stat_summary()`).
## Warning: Removed 3 rows containing missing values (`geom_segment()`).

#ridge plot: seperate density plots 
ggplot(weather_df, aes(x = tmax, y = name)) + 
  geom_density_ridges(scale = .85)
## Picking joint bandwidth of 1.54
## Warning: Removed 17 rows containing non-finite values
## (`stat_density_ridges()`).

# Saving and embedding plots

ggp_weather = weather_df |> 
  ggplot(aes(x=tmin,y=tmax)) + 
  geom_point()

ggsave("./ggp_weather.pdf",ggp_weather)
